I think its legs are tilted.

00:37:04.760 --> 00:37:06.760
But I guess it’s okay.

00:37:08.225 --> 00:37:09.155
It’s all right.

00:37:19.289 --> 00:37:19.969
Hey.

00:37:19.969 --> 00:37:20.561
Yeah?

00:37:20.561 --> 00:37:21.236
Wanna grab something to eat?

00:37:22.071 --> 00:37:23.239
You go ahead.

00:37:28.225 --> 00:37:29.192
What are you doing here, Uncle Jim?

00:37:30.236 --> 00:37:31.229
Shopping.

00:37:31.544 --> 00:37:33.074
Almost done here. I’m headed home.

00:37:34.385 --> 00:37:35.464
You?

00:37:39.113 --> 00:37:39.935
Uncle Jim,

00:37:41.779 --> 00:37:42.714
want to grab something to eat?

00:37:54.568 --> 00:37:55.159
Wow.

00:37:55.499 --> 00:37:57.199
They have lots of customers every day?

00:37:57.199 --> 00:37:57.920
Yeah.

00:37:57.920 --> 00:37:59.302
It’s typical.

00:37:59.302 --> 00:38:02.396
It’s packed with customers from around noon to 3 p.m.

00:38:02.396 --> 00:38:04.566
People who work nearby come to eat here.

00:38:06.261 --> 00:38:10.202
I thought you ate in the mall every day as you work there.

00:38:10.430 --> 00:38:11.477
Come on.

00:38:11.890 --> 00:38:12.843
In the mall?

00:38:13.391 --> 00:38:15.537
It’s pricey. Like 200 baht per meal.

00:38:15.537 --> 00:38:17.918
If I do that, I won’t have any money left to save.

00:38:18.749 --> 00:38:20.749
You seem to get a nice salary.

00:38:22.330 --> 00:38:23.445
Not really.

00:38:23.979 --> 00:38:28.116
If so, I wouldn’t work an extra job at your diner.

00:38:37.688 --> 00:38:38.644
Is it good, Uncle?

00:38:47.965 --> 00:38:49.722
One fresh mango, please.

00:38:50.379 --> 00:38:51.270
Want some fruit?

00:38:51.925 --> 00:38:52.743
Sure.

00:38:52.743 --> 00:38:54.207
20 baht, please.

00:38:54.785 --> 00:38:56.445
A 500-baht bill?

00:38:56.445 --> 00:38:57.264
Let me go break it.

00:38:57.264 --> 00:38:59.786
It’s okay. I'll come get the change tomorrow.

00:38:59.786 --> 00:39:01.105
Sure. Thank you.

00:39:01.757 --> 00:39:02.771
Hello.

00:39:02.771 --> 00:39:03.611
Hello, Wen.

00:39:03.611 --> 00:39:04.628
Can I have my regular, please?

00:39:04.628 --> 00:39:06.412
Of course. Four bags, right?

00:39:06.638 --> 00:39:08.225
Did she need to be in such a hurry?

00:39:08.415 --> 00:39:09.147
Her?

00:39:09.657 --> 00:39:10.731
She did, Uncle.

00:39:11.017 --> 00:39:13.648
If she is late, her pay will be deducted by the minute.

00:39:13.907 --> 00:39:14.759
She must hurry.

00:39:15.244 --> 00:39:18.819
If this rule applies at the diner, Leng won’t have any money left.

00:39:21.022 --> 00:39:21.947
So…

00:39:22.651 --> 00:39:24.211
where do you normally have lunch?

00:39:24.919 --> 00:39:27.234
Sometimes, I buy. Sometimes, I cook.

00:39:27.234 --> 00:39:29.070
But I don’t usually wake up to have lunch.

00:39:29.070 --> 00:39:31.203
I eat whatever Leng buys for me.

00:39:33.226 --> 00:39:34.294
Yours is ready, Wen.

00:39:34.440 --> 00:39:35.712
Thank you.

00:39:36.425 --> 00:39:37.029
Here you go.

00:39:37.029 --> 00:39:37.867
Thank you.

00:39:37.867 --> 00:39:38.826
See you.

00:39:38.826 --> 00:39:40.453
Come again tomorrow.

00:39:41.876 --> 00:39:42.678
Want some?

00:39:44.717 --> 00:39:46.279
It was a big profit.

00:39:46.523 --> 00:39:49.348
100 baht can get you everything in my market.

00:39:49.954 --> 00:39:54.866
But these are peeled, come with sticks, and salt and chili dip.

00:39:57.205 --> 00:39:59.569
Uncle, I need to get back to work.

00:39:59.569 --> 00:40:00.425
I’ll see you later.

00:40:01.006 --> 00:40:02.118
Are you coming this evening?

00:40:05.467 --> 00:40:06.355
Of course, I’m coming.

00:40:08.225 --> 00:40:11.657
My work is easy. Point a finger and give orders. That’s all.

00:40:12.127 --> 00:40:13.933
I have so much time for you.

00:40:17.430 --> 00:40:19.940
Your job seems fun.

00:40:21.774 --> 00:40:23.386
Selling Chicken Rice is more pleasurable.

00:40:28.436 --> 00:40:30.630
Uncle, I’m taking off.

00:40:31.693 --> 00:40:32.397
Here.

00:40:33.101 --> 00:40:34.979
Don’t you want it at all?

00:40:35.885 --> 00:40:36.743
Well…

00:40:38.029 --> 00:40:39.171
I’ll take one piece.

00:40:47.762 --> 00:40:48.669
Don’t forget.

00:40:48.960 --> 00:40:49.625
Hm?

00:40:49.625 --> 00:40:50.677
To eat.

00:40:51.841 --> 00:40:53.404
Bye.

00:41:08.887 --> 00:41:10.105
We should play football together again.

00:41:10.105 --> 00:41:10.887
Sure.

00:41:10.887 --> 00:41:13.396
How about this Saturday? Are you free?

00:41:17.760 --> 00:41:18.577
Hey.

00:41:19.135 --> 00:41:20.803
We better hurry.

00:41:20.803 --> 00:41:21.750
Golf said the pizza has been served.

00:41:21.750 --> 00:41:23.421
You go ahead. I’ll catch up with you.

00:41:24.067 --> 00:41:25.010
Go.

00:41:26.067 --> 00:41:27.124
Spare me some.

00:41:27.124 --> 00:41:28.266
All right. Come quickly.

00:41:32.783 --> 00:41:33.518
Li Ming.

00:41:34.416 --> 00:41:35.273
Wen.

00:41:35.945 --> 00:41:36.985
Hello.

00:41:42.702 --> 00:41:43.765
Wanna join Work &amp; Travel?

00:41:44.702 --> 00:41:46.464
I want to go to the states.

00:41:47.291 --> 00:41:49.655
Or somewhere affordable.

00:41:51.592 --> 00:41:53.225
Why don’t you walk in and talk to her?

00:41:55.294 --> 00:41:56.481
I don’t know the language.

00:42:00.752 --> 00:42:02.924
America and Australia?

00:42:04.536 --> 00:42:07.895
Where would you choose if you could?

00:42:10.681 --> 00:42:12.196
It actually depends on the person.

00:42:12.587 --> 00:42:14.587
And the money you have.

00:42:15.208 --> 00:42:18.494
I’d choose America as I think it’s more interesting.

00:42:18.666 --> 00:42:20.666
Besides, I have some relatives there.

00:42:21.298 --> 00:42:22.189
You do?

00:42:22.189 --> 00:42:22.983
Yeah.

00:42:23.268 --> 00:42:27.465
Then can I ask you if I need some advice?

00:42:27.465 --> 00:42:28.755
Of course.

00:42:29.451 --> 00:42:31.451
You can message me.

00:42:31.451 --> 00:42:32.470
Here’s my chat ID.

00:42:42.076 --> 00:42:44.294
Have you asked Uncle Jim though?

00:43:14.052 --> 00:43:14.897
Hey.

00:43:15.674 --> 00:43:16.463
Hey.

00:43:18.745 --> 00:43:19.560
Hey.

00:43:30.314 --> 00:43:32.314
Ah. You want to wash it yourself?

00:43:33.058 --> 00:43:34.010
Thanks a lot.

00:43:40.829 --> 00:43:42.799
I have nothing to do tonight.

00:43:53.095 --> 00:43:54.464
Are you asking me to watch a movie?

00:44:07.317 --> 00:44:10.094
I want to watch a Thai movie, but there are no subtitles.

00:44:19.191 --> 00:44:21.943
Can you tell me what happens in the key scenes?

00:44:26.144 --> 00:44:28.824
You’re ordering me around…

00:44:30.486 --> 00:44:32.316
You’re ordering me around like I’m your minion.

00:44:47.292 --> 00:44:48.831
[I see you can understand it just fine.]

00:45:02.457 --> 00:45:03.785
[I can guess the main idea. But for some scenes, I can’t. I want to know what’s going on.]

00:45:11.935 --> 00:45:13.935
[All right. Next time, let me know which one you want to watch. I watch it with you.]

00:45:21.704 --> 00:45:22.711
For what?

00:45:23.225 --> 00:45:24.218
Oh, right.

00:45:27.665 --> 00:45:29.204
[For what?]

00:45:33.245 --> 00:45:35.245
[For being my ears.]

00:45:40.185 --> 00:45:42.331
[Should we catch a movie at the cinema next time?]

00:45:46.879 --> 00:45:47.908
Wanna go?

00:46:00.377 --> 00:46:04.246
[I can’t. Ever since I went deaf, my mom forbids me from going out.]

00:46:39.824 --> 00:46:40.572
Leng.

00:46:40.960 --> 00:46:41.848
Yes, Uncle?

00:46:42.532 --> 00:46:43.251
Here.

00:46:43.639 --> 00:46:44.677
My gift for you.

00:46:45.262 --> 00:46:46.213
What now?

00:46:46.528 --> 00:46:47.747
I bet they’re leftovers again.

00:46:56.335 --> 00:46:57.521
Why dressed up today?

00:46:58.225 --> 00:46:59.039
Where did you go?

00:46:59.319 --> 00:47:00.276
I ran an errand.

00:47:01.926 --> 00:47:02.969
What errand?

00:47:04.042 --> 00:47:04.947
None of your business.

00:47:12.082 --> 00:47:13.177
Whose gold necklace?

00:47:17.475 --> 00:47:18.352
Here.

00:47:20.342 --> 00:47:21.465
I bought it for you.

00:47:24.160 --> 00:47:25.375
It’s Praew’s dowry.

00:47:29.306 --> 00:47:30.334
Are you serious?

00:47:41.653 --> 00:47:43.225
Don’t you sell it.

00:47:46.762 --> 00:47:47.716
Uncle, thank you.

00:47:47.716 --> 00:47:48.762
Leng!

00:47:48.926 --> 00:47:49.857
I’m giving you a reward.

00:47:49.857 --> 00:47:51.120
I don’t want your damn reward.

00:47:51.120 --> 00:47:53.822
- Leng, back to your seat.
- Go ahead, Leng.

00:48:03.107 --> 00:48:04.142
What about you?

00:48:04.263 --> 00:48:05.228
What’s going on?

00:48:05.772 --> 00:48:07.481
One during the day, another at night.

00:48:08.018 --> 00:48:09.190
Why don’t you pick one?

00:48:11.520 --> 00:48:13.003
Be respectful, Leng.

00:48:14.700 --> 00:48:16.190
Get serious with someone.

00:48:16.613 --> 00:48:17.561
Kill your loneliness.

00:48:20.959 --> 00:48:22.399
How do you know I’m lonely?

00:48:23.978 --> 00:48:25.978
Well, we’re all destined to pair up with someone.

00:48:26.646 --> 00:48:29.253
I can't stay with you forever, you know?

00:48:29.253 --> 00:48:30.533
I’m having a wife. See?

00:48:30.923 --> 00:48:32.705
Just deal with your own business.

00:48:32.705 --> 00:48:33.822
Don’t you worry about me.

00:48:35.984 --> 00:48:36.945
I’m going to see Praew.

00:48:36.945 --> 00:48:37.499
Yes.

00:48:37.750 --> 00:48:38.539
Thank you, Uncle Jim.

00:48:38.539 --> 00:48:39.386
Here.

00:48:48.648 --> 00:48:49.507
Is it good?

00:48:57.996 --> 00:48:59.141
Hello.

00:49:00.888 --> 00:49:01.743
What did you say?

00:49:06.377 --> 00:49:07.410
We’re parking.

00:49:07.410 --> 00:49:08.377
Shit!

00:49:10.471 --> 00:49:11.743
I gotta go.

00:49:11.872 --> 00:49:14.260
If we’re to compensate you, how much would you ask?

00:49:14.260 --> 00:49:16.554
3,000 THB would do. I’m in a hurry here.

00:49:41.361 --> 00:49:42.631
Almost there.

00:49:42.878 --> 00:49:43.855
We’re parking.

00:49:43.855 --> 00:49:45.005
Shit!

00:49:46.907 --> 00:49:48.031
I gotta go.

00:49:52.740 --> 00:49:53.770
Are you guys all right?

00:49:55.813 --> 00:49:56.536
Gosh.

00:49:57.120 --> 00:49:58.116
Are you okay?

00:50:01.462 --> 00:50:03.117
You okay? Are you hurt?

00:50:03.304 --> 00:50:05.439
It hurts. My leg might be broken.

00:50:06.760 --> 00:50:10.000
Mister, why didn’t you look carefully when you reversed a car?

00:50:10.208 --> 00:50:12.208
We had the light on. Couldn't you see us?

00:50:13.907 --> 00:50:15.264
Sir, please calm.

00:50:16.162 --> 00:50:17.613
Uncle, do you have the car insurance?

00:50:18.240 --> 00:50:19.037
One sec.

00:50:20.564 --> 00:50:21.565
Are you all right?

00:50:25.245 --> 00:50:26.114
Clean your wound.

00:50:26.114 --> 00:50:26.920
[Kongsup Car Insurance]

00:50:27.715 --> 00:50:31.080
If we’re to compensate you, how much would you ask?

00:50:32.328 --> 00:50:34.520
3,000 THB would do. I’m in a hurry here.

00:50:40.433 --> 00:50:41.140
Uncle.

00:50:42.060 --> 00:50:43.353
What did the insurance staff say?

00:50:44.920 --> 00:50:45.932
He’s in a rush.

00:50:45.932 --> 00:50:47.391
He said we could pay him.

00:50:47.391 --> 00:50:49.759
Then you can deal with the insurance company later.

00:50:50.564 --> 00:50:51.682
How much is he asking?

00:50:51.862 --> 00:50:52.744
3,000 baht.

00:50:53.112 --> 00:50:53.815
3,000 baht?

00:50:54.466 --> 00:50:55.988
My car insurance just expired.

00:50:56.373 --> 00:50:57.873
I’ll pay him.

00:50:58.098 --> 00:50:59.480
Just tell him to wait a moment.

00:51:21.343 --> 00:51:23.163
I advanced it.

00:51:26.003 --> 00:51:27.035
I will transfer it back.

00:51:29.190 --> 00:51:30.158
It’s fine.

00:51:30.720 --> 00:51:33.720
This wouldn’t happen if I didn’t ask you to drop me off here.

00:51:34.093 --> 00:51:34.962
We can’t do that.

00:51:36.556 --> 00:51:37.687
Come on.

00:51:39.776 --> 00:51:41.240
Let’s talk later.

00:51:41.240 --> 00:51:42.266
I need to get to work now.

00:51:42.356 --> 00:51:43.130
Thank you.

00:51:44.601 --> 00:51:45.373
Hello.

00:51:46.601 --> 00:51:47.829
I’m almost there.

00:52:06.747 --> 00:52:08.119
We don’t have enough bats on this side.

00:52:08.501 --> 00:52:09.600
Why not?

00:52:10.199 --> 00:52:12.693
I think Jack sent us the wrong work file.

00:52:12.890 --> 00:52:13.721
Wrong file?

00:52:13.721 --> 00:52:14.374
Yeah.

00:52:17.226 --> 00:52:17.765
Damn it.

00:52:19.600 --> 00:52:21.061
Can we use black fabric instead?

00:52:22.164 --> 00:52:23.324
Don’t think it will look good.

00:52:24.164 --> 00:52:25.004
It’s weird.

00:52:25.819 --> 00:52:26.781
You’re right.

00:52:28.442 --> 00:52:30.064
We should put it up inside.

00:52:33.528 --> 00:52:34.653
Black papers work.

00:52:35.237 --> 00:52:36.539
But I think if we…

00:53:04.388 --> 00:53:05.737
You came yourself.

00:53:05.737 --> 00:53:06.367
I did.

00:53:08.937 --> 00:53:11.902
Great job you did here.

00:53:12.394 --> 00:53:13.521
Thank you, sir.

00:53:13.521 --> 00:53:15.202
Sorry though. It’s a little later than scheduled.

00:53:15.871 --> 00:53:17.339
Can I please get your chat ID?

00:53:17.676 --> 00:53:18.522
My chat ID?

00:53:18.522 --> 00:53:21.261
Yes. We can discuss work afterward.

00:53:21.643 --> 00:53:22.856
That’s awesome.

00:53:39.483 --> 00:53:40.563
Is this you?

00:54:04.136 --> 00:54:06.091
Does the beer here taste better than the beer at your diner?

00:54:17.204 --> 00:54:18.822
Beer tastes the same everywhere.

00:54:19.461 --> 00:54:20.817
How can it taste better?

00:54:24.813 --> 00:54:27.320
You are not romantic at all. You know that?

00:54:29.777 --> 00:54:31.777
When you’re almost 40 like me,

00:54:32.462 --> 00:54:34.282
with one nephew, one employee,

00:54:34.601 --> 00:54:37.589
a house, a car, and a money pool to deal with,

00:54:37.974 --> 00:54:39.186
you can’t afford to be romantic.

00:54:39.792 --> 00:54:41.231
Life is bitter.

00:54:42.320 --> 00:54:43.432
Bitter like beer?

00:54:45.004 --> 00:54:46.072
Beer is much sweeter in comparison.

00:54:47.320 --> 00:54:49.320
That’s why you drink it every day.

00:54:54.311 --> 00:54:56.199
I drink because I want to get drunk.

00:54:57.758 --> 00:54:58.997
When I’m drunk, I don’t dream.

00:54:59.940 --> 00:55:01.240
Just sleep and wake up.

00:55:05.197 --> 00:55:06.247
Do you have a dream?

00:55:08.470 --> 00:55:11.283
My dream isn’t romantic.

00:55:13.130 --> 00:55:14.159
Pay off my debt.

00:55:14.720 --> 00:55:16.028
Financially support my nephew until he graduates.

00:55:18.545 --> 00:55:20.837
And I’d like to experience having a million baht.

00:55:20.837 --> 00:55:21.864
See what it’s like.

00:55:22.775 --> 00:55:23.675
What is yours?

00:55:41.989 --> 00:55:43.027
I want home.

00:55:47.450 --> 00:55:50.365
Home where someone waits for me.

00:55:52.114 --> 00:55:53.643
When I get home, all my tiredness is gone.

00:55:54.816 --> 00:55:56.277
When I’m home, I have peace of mind.

00:55:59.114 --> 00:56:01.114
Not just a place to sleep.

00:56:05.852 --> 00:56:07.156
Don’t you already have one?

00:56:09.694 --> 00:56:10.713
I don’t.

00:56:26.450 --> 00:56:27.341
Don’t.

00:56:31.415 --> 00:56:32.135
It’s not good.

00:56:35.009 --> 00:56:38.512
If you don’t try, how can you tell if it’s good or not?

00:56:57.925 --> 00:56:58.947
Okay, Uncle.

00:56:59.710 --> 00:57:00.688
I get it.

00:57:03.149 --> 00:57:04.581
I see I’m not the right person.

00:57:05.906 --> 00:57:07.686
Sorry for making you uncomfortable.

00:57:07.686 --> 00:57:08.369
Hey.

00:57:09.008 --> 00:57:09.881
I’m okay.

00:57:11.138 --> 00:57:12.265
You will be okay too.

00:57:18.333 --> 00:57:21.433
Can you lend me your shoulder?

00:57:27.078 --> 00:57:27.879
Why should I?

00:57:29.600 --> 00:57:30.619
As an acquaintance, if you don't mind

00:57:53.075 --> 00:57:54.828
Don’t waste your time on me.

00:58:00.669 --> 00:58:01.606
Someone like me

00:58:04.749 --> 00:58:06.598
doesn’t fit to be anyone’s home.

00:58:50.676 --> 00:58:54.315
Directed by Noppharnach Chaiyahwimhon

00:58:54.960 --> 00:58:56.720
I used to argue with my sister.

00:58:56.720 --> 00:59:00.162
She claimed that man-to-man love does not exist.

00:59:00.162 --> 00:59:01.402
Do you know what I said to her?

00:59:01.480 --> 00:59:02.513
I said, “I’ll show you.”

00:59:02.760 --> 00:59:04.600
What a cunning son you are.

00:59:06.201 --> 00:59:09.000
Tell me which faculty or university you want to go to.

00:59:09.171 --> 00:59:11.720
Do you still need your uncle to make school decisions for you?

00:59:11.720 --> 00:59:12.908
What do you want to be?

00:59:12.908 --> 00:59:14.541
I don’t know yet.

00:59:15.018 --> 00:59:16.838
Do you want to go Loy Krathong together?
